Spain Beats Switzerland 2-0 for European Under-21 Soccer Title

-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 
2011-06-25T21:01:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-25/spain-beats-switzerland-2-0-for-european-under-21-soccer-title.html
Spain  beat Switzerland 2-0 in the
final of the European Under-21 Soccer Championship in Aarhus,
Denmark.  Ander Herrera gave Spain the lead with a header in the 41st
minute, the first goal allowed by the Swiss in five games in the
tournament. Thiago Alcantara then clinched the victory with nine
minutes left with a long free kick after goalkeeper Yann Sommer
had come off his line.  It’s the third Under-21 title for Spain, second-most behind
 Italy ’s five.  Belarus beat the Czech Republic 1-0 in the third-place game
earlier today in Aalborg.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  